---
const pageTitle = "About Me";

const identity = {
    name: "Erwin Tzac",
    country: "Belize",
    occupation: "Tech Sales",
    hobbies: ["Reading", "Traveling", "Coding"]
};

const skills = ["HTML", "CSS", "JavaScript", "Astro", "Git", "GitHub", "Cold Calling"];

const happy = true;
const finished = false;
const goal = 3;

---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
</head>
<body>
    <a href="/">Home</a>
    <a href="/about">About</a>
    <a href="/blog">Blog</a>
    <h1>{pageTitle}</h1>
    <h2>... and my new Astro site</h2>
    <p>Welcome to the about page of my Astro site. Here you can find more information about the project and its purpose.</p>
    <p>This site will update as I complete more of the tutorial, so keep checking back and see how my journey is going!</p>

    <p>Here are a few facts about me: </p>

    <ul>
        <li>My name is {identity.name}</li>
        <li>I live in {identity.country} and I work as {identity.occupation}</li>
        {identity.hobbies.length >=2 && 
            <li>Two of my hobbies are: {identity.hobbies[0]} and {identity.hobbies[1]}</li>
        }
    </ul>

    <p>Here are some of the web development skills I have learned so far:</p>

    <ul>
        {skills.map((skill) => (
            <li>{skill}</li>
        ))}
        
    </ul>

    {happy && <p>I am happy to share my journey and learn Astro!</p>}
    {finished && <p>I have finished the Astro tutorial!</p>}
    {goal === 3 ? <p>My goal is to finish in 3 days or less! </p> : <p>My goal is not 3 days.</p>}
    
</body>
</html>
